    "phase_11_notes": [
      "@objc + @MainActor: @objc methods on @MainActor-inferred classes (via NSApplicationDelegate protocol annotation) do NOT automatically inherit @MainActor isolation in Swift 6. Calling a @MainActor-isolated method (FloatingWindow.ensureOnScreen, inherited from NSPanel) from a plain @objc func produces a 'call to main actor-isolated instance method in synchronous nonisolated context' warning. Fix: explicit @MainActor annotation on the selector method.",
      "Selector-based addObserver for @Sendable constraint: NotificationCenter.addObserver(forName:object:queue:using:) requires @Sendable closure. Capturing DexterApp (non-Sendable, NSApplicationDelegate) in a @Sendable closure triggers 'capture of self with non-Sendable type in @Sendable closure'. Selector-based addObserver(_:selector:name:object:) has no @Sendable constraint \u2014 the ObjC message dispatch mechanism doesn't participate in Swift's actor system \u2014 eliminating both warnings cleanly.",
      "NSStringFromRect / NSRectFromString coordinate system: AppKit window frames are always in points, not pixels. Both functions operate on the same point-coordinate system, so round-tripping through UserDefaults is exact. NSRectFromString returns NSZeroRect for unparseable strings \u2014 the guard against this prevents a silent zero-origin window placement on corrupt defaults.",
      "Center-point containment in loadOrDefaultFrame: Validation uses center-point containment (screen.frame.contains(center)) rather than full-frame containment. A window whose center is on a live screen is draggable to a fully on-screen position; full-frame containment would be overly aggressive and reset positions that are merely partially clipped near a screen edge.",
      "applicationWillTerminate synchronous flush: The 250ms debounce DispatchWorkItem may not fire before process exit if the operator quits immediately after dragging. applicationWillTerminate calls persistFrameNow() synchronously before the process exits. Since persistFrameNow() is idempotent (harmless duplicate write if debounce already fired), this is a zero-downside guarantee.",
      "defaultFrame() uses visibleFrame not frame: visibleFrame excludes the Dock and menu bar, so the 80pt y-offset is above the Dock rather than behind it. This matches the Phase 1 convention (init() used visibleFrame.minY + 20)."
    ],
    "phase_12_criteria": {
      "1_swift_build_clean": "PASS \u2014 swift build completes with 0 errors, 0 warnings from project code; only pre-existing grpc-swift deprecation warnings in generated dexter.grpc.swift remain",
      "note": "Manual acceptance criteria (Metal disc renders, click-through, entity state changes, action dialogs, gRPC no regression) require make run to verify."
    },
    "phase_12_notes": [
      "SwiftPM cannot compile .metal files: There is no .metal compilation target in SwiftPM. Metal shader bytecode must come from elsewhere. Runtime MTLDevice.makeLibrary(source:options:) with an inline MSL string constant is the correct solution \u2014 no .metal file, no resource bundle entry, produces identical GPU bytecode to offline compilation.",
      "MTKView + bitmapImageRepForCachingDisplay: MTKView renders through CAMetalLayer which bypasses the standard NSView compositing path. bitmapImageRepForCachingDisplay returns a zero-alpha bitmap for Metal content \u2014 PassthroughView's bitmap cache would see the disc as fully transparent and pass all clicks through. Fix: override hitTest(_:) in AnimatedEntity with circle SDF math that matches the shader geometry.",
      "Circle SDF hitTest radius derivation: The shader uses aspect-correct coordinates where the shorter dimension maps to 1.0 in shader space (y spans -1\u20261). A disc of shader baseRadius = 0.55 occupies 0.55 \u00d7 (min(w,h) / 2) NSView points. For a 200\u00d7400pt window: 0.55 \u00d7 100 = 55pt. Using 0.4 \u00d7 min(w,h) = 80pt (naive formula) would make the click area ~45% larger than the visible disc.",
      "MainActor.run async-body overload removed in Swift 6: Swift 6 removed the async-body overload of MainActor.run to prevent accidental main-actor-executor starvation (the async body would hold the MainActor executor while suspended, blocking other @MainActor work). The replacement: withCheckedContinuation + Task { @MainActor in }. The Task creates a new cooperative task isolated to @MainActor; the continuation bridges the result back to the awaiting actor context.",
